    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2230</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dern</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-23">April 23,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Referring to previous
                    correspondence in reference to limitations being placed on work which was
                    requested <pb facs="0457" n="387" xml:id="pg_387"/> of The Panama Canal to be
                    done on the Peruvian Cruiser <hi rend="italic">Bolognesi</hi>, and particularly
                    to my letter of April 17th quoting the Governor’s radiogram of the 12th instant
                    advising, among other things, that this cruiser arrived on the 10th instant,
                    there is quoted hereunder the following self-explanatory radio received from the
                    Governor under date of the 21st instant: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Confidential—Peruvian Cruiser <hi rend="italic">Bolognesi</hi> sailed
                            from Balboa yesterday afternoon. Understand going to Callao.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The above quoted message was read to a representative of the State Department
                    over the telephone on the 21st instant.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. H. Dern</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
